  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nSuppose you have a migrations file, but no actual migrations occur in it.  When you run `truffle migrate`, the total cost is printed as `0 undefined`, rather than `0 wei` or `0 ether` or just `0`.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate a new Truffle project, edit `1_initial_migrations.js` by removing the `deployer.deploy` line, then try migrating your project.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe 0 costs should not have \"undefined\" displayed as their unit.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\nStarting migrations...\r\n======================\r\n> Network name:    'development'\r\n> Network id:      1636404659203\r\n> Block gas limit: 12000000 (0xb71b00)\r\n\r\n\r\n1_initial_migration.js\r\n======================\r\n   -------------------------------------\r\n   > Total cost:                   0 undefined\r\n\r\n\r\nSummary\r\n=======\r\n> Total deployments:   0\r\n> Final cost:          0 undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.18",
